Medicare and MDVIP
I talked to Hinchman’s office\. They said  I should keep both MDVIP and Medicare\. I should start with a bare bones Medicare supplement or advantage plan\. They take Aetna, Blue Cross, Signa, United Health Care\.

entries.text:
The Fainting Spell
This is the day I fainted at Peaks Athletic. I did 30 minutes on the AMT machine. Then I did progressive bicep curls - 15lbs- 20-25. After that, I felt nauseous so I sat down for a bit until is passed. I set up the leg press machine, sat down in it then passed out. I woke up in the ambulance.

Turned in Direct Deposit
Turned in direct deposit form with cancelled check to Rose Hough at Basha’s.

Cancelled Accounts
Cancelled personal account at DG Community bank. Cancelled Chase Freedom CC account.

Bought Pocket Watch
Bought “Vintage Bulls eye Pocket Watch” on eBay. it was listed as a non-working watch for parts only. My intention is to try and fix it and sell it. If I fail to fix it, I’ll keep it for parts.

It’s fixed and running. Let’s see how long.

Gave Ambulance Company info

Called Citibank

Heart Info Sent

The Pendleton said that the charge to Chase Freedom was accepted.

Look into the Hunter brand remote for the office fan. If it works, we’ll retro-fit them into the other fans.

After getting an oil change for Mica and Lynns doctor visit, we spent a beautiful day off. We bought a pound of coffee for Sheila Casperson. Then we bought our first humming bird feeder. In the late afternoon we organized our 2016 taxes.

R Hough Gives Days off 2/7 to 2/10

Said that I show no signs of a seizure and that it was probably a vasovagal syncope.

Changed Battery
Changed battery in bedroom fan remote.

Stuffed Quesadillas
Hiva taught me how to make stuffed Quesadillas

Called Rose Hough
She said I’m on the Basha’s schedule 2/6 1-9pm

Sky Harbor Apt Parking
I called about reserved parking. They said it’s only for the $25 lots/

AutoPay

Rose and Hiva went nuts because the health department was there. Rose told me to sanitize the slicers, one at a time, during the day.

Talked to Stromberg about leasing 5143 Mochel. 
He needs Fed ID and a copy of the lease.

Breakfast with Frank Iacovelli
Talked about many things including flying. He wants to buy another plane and wants me to go with him to a glider field to possibly get a GCFI and tow.

Nancy Olivi
Has CJD. It might be aggressive and she is very ill. I might have to go to Chicago on short notice.

Craig Hudson
Doubled over in pain due to gall bladder problems.

Jarecki & Nicholas
I sent them both contact information.

eBay
yu-yujoy bought another fusto. I asked Bill Jarecki to send one with a chromed-brass spigot.

JR Walker

JR Walker 
Check send FedEx, # 808351759654

It turns out that Assurant is an AMAC plan. Lynn and I decided to stay with Assurant and therefore with Dr Sobek.

Walgreens
Got 20 mg 90 day supply of Atorvastatin and was charged $392.89. I went home and Googled for other options. I found that I get a discount card with my health insurance that brought the price down to about $250. I also found a deal on Walgreen’s web site for a $30/month discount card.

I went back to Walgreens to find out if I have any other options. The pharmacist looked up options and found one that brought the price down to $52.66. She refunded $340.23 from my credit card.

Gun Club With the Kids
Went to the Rio Salado sportman's club with Ron, Rick and Lori. Had a great time. Lori tried the shotgun once, but almost got knocked over by the recoil.

Shipped two HP ink tanks in USPS small priority boxes.

flies home today

His wake was today. J Turner attended and  told Joanne that we are thinking of her and the family. J forwarded the link to the funeral home that we sent, to Roberta Flanders and she sent it to the DG market vendors.

Checked the DG bank web site. OliveLynn has $4000 of new transfers from Discover bank and savings. Should have enough coverage through mid-March.

Dental stuff
I bit down hard and felt a little pain in a tooth yesterday.  I called Dr Sobek and got an appointment. She thinks I need a crown and possibly a root canal. She recommended an endodontist and I got an appointment for Friday 8am.

Dental
Went to Dr Sluyk. I do have a cracked tooth, but Dr can't see how deep it is. He recommends that I get it prepped for a crown, then Dr Sobek will be able to see how deep the crack is.

Talked to Tammy Abbott (AMAC) about health insurance renewal/replacement. Looks like AZ allows only 90 day renewal. Current policy ends on 5/11/17. She says I should cancel my UH plan effective 3/30/17 and she can apply for a new plan effective 3/31 until 12/31/2017.

Completed application for United Healthcare for a plan from 3/31/17 for 184 days.

Glasshopper Schor

I got a call from Larry Dumdie. He said that the materials should arrive next week and I gave him Dan Nicholas’s phone number.

WB Bottle
Called W Morrison. She said she would send me samples of after shave bottles.

Baseball
Went to a game with the Missus. KC vs CO.

Gloria Spinato
I went to Gloria's apartment to install her new phone. She has an old-fashioned voice mail recorder where you plug the recorder to the incoming phone line then connect the phone to the recorder. 

The phone itself is a little complicated in that it takes four button strikes to call Elaine.

Glasshoppper Schor
I called: Left message for Larry to call me.

Glasshopper Shor
I called. The lady said that she will stress to Larry to call me back. I reminded her that it’s been since 2/8/17 since we got an estimate from them.

Jennie Kunze
I called to find the best way to transfer information. We agreed that a regular letter is fine. She will also confirm that she has a cop of our living wills.

Glasshopper Shor
I talked to Larry. He said that the door frames should arrive Friday 3/24. Then he will order the glass which should come late the next week. Therefore, installation should happen the week of 4/3.

Downers Grove

ACH Payments
Contacted Strip by email to ask for information. PayPal, amazon and etc, charge 2.9% per transaction and did not advertise ACH payments.

I talked to the lady owner. They apparently dropped the ball and did not tell the guy to call us to measure the screens.

WB Bottle
I opened the sample and they are fine. I then called Wanda to ask for pump bottle samples and if she can send one case to start. She will get back to me on this one.

Basil
Sowed 4 cells in the Burpee starter thing today.

WB Bottle
I called Wanda to say that I liked many of her offers. But I told her that I need a lotion pump too. She will get back to me.

Fusti

ROMANWAYOFSHAVING.COM
I just bought this URL

Scottsdale Physicians Group

I enrolled in $2500 of firearms insurance.

Federal 2016 income tax refund came.

DWOLLA

I talked to Bret at the Arizona Corporation Commission. He said the TCIRPSO Corp is in progress. I will be notified of the status by eMail. I should wait for that before applying for a sales tax or EIN.

Just got 10/10 at the range. That qualified me.

Lightspeed

Used GTA to get onto Elaine’s computer and do minor adjustments. Had a little trouble with her logging in,

Scottsdale Physicians Group

Screens
Posted an add in Nextdoor.com to give the screens away.

ConstitutionAlly

Installed a new receiver and transmitter.
Visited beautiful old Spanish mission just outside of Tucson. A great day with the missus.
Stayed here overnight. First Tucson trip.

Visited with the missus for a great day.

A walk around the Fountain. Then a relaxing coffee.

DWOLLA
OliveLynn has been reinstated and my DWOLLA account is set up.

OliveLynn
Re-instated!!!!!

I upgraded to Version 6 and it did not accept my old license. I sent an email to support.

My first ride from 11500 E Cochise to the Fountain in Fountain Hills.

Roman Way

Spinato’s Sprinklers

Was hacked again. The Citibank person said that they contact recurring payees to tell them that the card number has changed. Apparently, one of those payees is the culprit??? She said that they will turn off the feature and send me another card.

Contacted Theresa Schultz

TCISPRO
Deposited $800 to cover credit card payment.

Wedding of Sam Hudson and Allison Burrel in South Bend, IN area. Ron, Rick, Hope, Elaine, Marilyn, Anthony, Jaime, Ella, Eva, Cole and Kennedy, all from AZ attended.
Bought Hi-Point 9mm carbine.

Saw our first one today. I smacked it with a broom and threw it out the back.

Rio Salado Sportsmen’s Club
Went to the gun range with Ron. Shot about 50 rounds through the Hi-Point 9mm. Found that the front sight can loosen up.

Wet Shaving Products
Chinese, assembled in Ca;ifornia.

Shaving Bowls
I left a voice mail and sent an email to David Ray to talk about him making shaving bowls for me to included in Roman Way gift sets.

Fountain Hills Farmers Market
Hopefully, I sent in all required information including insurance info.
I verified there is an Ethereum balance in my Blockchain wallet. It’s visible on the internet, but not in the iPhone app. I submitted a ticket asking how to  make it visible on the app.

Smoke detectors

Called Revel
I’m to ask a manager to add me as an employee to Revel. So, I sent an email to Jackie Weiss with this request.
Charging Ring Doorbell

iPhone Problems
Having lots of trouble with my iPhone 6. It does not maintain a strong WiFi or Bluetooth signal. I chatted with a genius: he ran diagnostics to check software and said that it checked out fine. I went to the Apple store: the genius ran diagnostics and said that the hardware was fine.  I suspect the internals are getting loose due to bike rides, I need to stop using the handlebar mount.

I restored the phone several times, to no avail. Note that apps loose internal information when this happens. I need to find how to restore Google Authenticator because it doesn’t seem to keep information.

Fountain Hills Great Fair 2018
Submitted an application for the fair

Shiftgig
Sent application to shiftgig.com

GoShare

GoShare
Not Available in AZ.

Health Insurance

Kraken

Mike Cassa

5143 Mochel
I talked to Mike Phillips. He will check with Greenscape to find out if we have to have condo meetings. I told him a little history of the building that I bought it from Greenscape in 2012.

APS
Talked to agent about “lite choice” plan. This plan assumes usage at average of 600 kWh/month. Our average is 601. I asked about the change from gas to a heat pump. She said, there’s no harm, but next year we will be reviewed and if we’re over 600 kWh/month they will recommend premier choice.

Health Insurance

Health Insurance

Logmein
I was charged $642.30 for a subscription last night on AMEX Gold. I tried to log in and was unsuccessful because they still had olivelynn@icloud.com. I called to get the charge reversed. The guy named Yary said that I did in fact close my account April 2017.

Smoke Detectors

Netflix
Cancelled DVD account

Scottsdale Pathology
I called IHC insurance and talked to Jas. She said that the claim was received on 12/7/17. It was processed on 12/13/17. On 1/3/18, they requested more information from the doctor and the claim is still pending.

Then I called Scottsdale Pathology’s collection agency and talked to Dave. He said that they first sent the claim to the wrong insurance company but then sent it to IHC (BTW, they had IAC on file instead of IHC). He agrees that the claim is still pending and I don’t owe any money.

5143 Mochel Dr
Downers Grove SOLD!!!

Kitchen Wall Clock
Changed batteries.

CAF

CAF

CO Alarm
Changed batteries

We talked to Laura at IHC today. She said that they judged that the January 2017 syncope is a pre-existing condition of the October 2017 TGA . She said that they received the letter from Arizona Neurology (Shaya) on 4/10/18 and it is in process. They need a similar appeal from the Hospital for their bills. We forwarded this information on to Maureen Javan at Honor Health.

Mike Maderazzo
He complained about problems with scanning and using DropBox. I used GoToAssist to get into his computer and discovered that the scanning defaults that I set up last time were gone. I doubt that the scanning program was still there. After trying to fix the problems with the apps he had installed, I downloaded and installed the driver package for his Brother DCP-7064DN printer. This gave him a new scanner interface that allowed him to scan to a .PDF file and safe to a folder of his choice.

Then I check an email he got that had a link to a file stored in DropBox. After investigating, I stumbled onto the fact that he has a DropBox account (I don’t know if it’s paid or free) and used it to forward the file to OfficeMax. The OfficeMax store in question cannot accept DropBox files, so I helped Mike copy the file to a Jump-Drive so that he could take it to the OfficeMax store,

IHC Insurance
I talked to Shyrisse. She said that they got the appeal letter from Shaya, but nothing from Honor Health.

Honor Health
I talked to Thomas. He said that the hospital filed an appeal to IHC on 4/24/18 and got a response back on 5/9/18 denying the claim. Thomas will be sending me the appeal documents.

IHC Insurance
I called and talked to Aretha. She said that the Arizona Neurology appeal was in process and that AzNe sent in a claim for the 4/2/18 consultation with Shaya, they should not have. Aretha also said that Honor Health has not sent in an appeal.

Honor Health
I talked to Maureen. She checked the files and all of my contacts with the hospital are recorded. She says that the hospital keeps contacting the insurance and IHC keeps refusing it to the hospital. I need to talk to Elsa in the insurance department at 623-334-6755, and that number doesn’t work. Maureen tries that number and it didn’t work for her either.

Honor Health
I talked to Elsa. She said that the insurance repeatedly denied the claim. I then called IHC and spoke to Aretha. Aretha said that they denied the claim, but the appeal is still under review.

Honor Health
I talked to Elsa. I told there that IHC said that the Hospital did not submit an appeal, but Elsa insists that the hospital did. Elsa will talk to her supervisor to find out what to do next. Elsa also suggested that I ask Maureen at Honor Health for a settlement amount.

Arizona Neurology
I called and talked to Alex. I offered to pay in full if they could discount the bill and that I would pay cash or check by the end of business today. She said that she would talk to her supervisor and call me back.

IHC Insurance
I talked to Brenda at 800-518-4510 about getting a copy of my policy. She said that I need to ask for a copy of the original application. She is sending it to me via email.

Honor Health
I talked to Christal. She directed me to a Basic Financial Assistance Uninsured form and said I’ll get an 81% discount. I got the form, signed it and emailed it to pas.assistance@honorhealth.com.

WB Bottle
I called Wanda to see if they would take back the Reid bottle caps. She said no because they were special order.

Mike Maderazzo
I helped him with large files through Drop Box and with his email signature. 1/2 hour, no charge today.

# Accident
Damage from accident between our Toyota Corolla and the Kia driven by Lue Neff\-Furnish 480\-606\-7903\. Paint scraping on our left front bumper, her car scraped from passenger door all the way to the rear tire well\. Photos attached\. Lue Neff\-Furnish License AZ AAS 3681\.

![](dayone-moment://E15DD8DCD660427687B1C4A196DA7F36)

![](dayone-moment://9AC26DA71DD441B295FD35A5F3A71034)

# Accident
Talked to Carlos from Traveller’s Insurance\. He took a statement from me and recorded it\. We both used Google Earth to describe the location of the accident, the orientation of the cars and how it happed\.

Lynn and I had just shopped at Home Depot at 7000 Mayo in Scottsdale\.  Our 2021 Toyota Corolla car was parked in a parking slot in the westbound direction\. There are parking slots all around, but no barriers, bumpers or other definition of the parking slot other than stripes painted on the pavement\. There were very few other parked cars\.  Our car was oriented such that I could pull out forward into the traffic lane\. We walked to our car\. I got in the drivers seat and Lynn in the passengers seat\. We both put our seat belts on\. I started the car, programmed the GPS and prepared to leave\. I cleared the right and left forward and began to pull out\. Lue Neff\-Furnish was driving westbound to get into a parking slot in front of us in the slots across the traffic lane\. She came up on my left, I didn’t see her\. I started to pull out and angle left when I saw her car too late to prevent the collision\.

# Accident
I was called by Briante at State Farm\. After some conversation, she told me that Lue was accusing me of not yielding right of way to her\. I denied that\. I told Briante that I started from a parking space and that Lue came up to me from my blind left side\.  I further told her that I have pictures and I uploaded them\. Briante asked me if I had any witnesses, and I said no\.

Then I talked to Carlos at Travellers and told him of the conversation with Briante\.

# Accident
Carlos called\. We’re OK to get Celeste fixed\. We’re not to worry about the other party, Traveller’s Ins will take care of that part\. Carlos is sure that we will not be held at fault\.

# Lynn’s Little Ray
\(Her new iPad\)
Received yesterday\.
We initialized it by a download from the iCloud/\.
The SSL S/MIME did not transfer properly and it would not create certificated/encrypted email\. It would not interpret encrypted emails\.
I talked to Jameson at Apple support and he is setting up a call with 2nd level support for the next Monday 7/12/2021\.

# Day One Essentials Guide
Welcome to Day One, we’re glad you’re here. If you’re wondering what you can do with your new journal, you’ve come to the right place. Below are a few of the features we believe will help you get the most out of Day One. 
 
 
1. **Photos**: Journal your favorite photos and say goodbye to the days of having your best shots get lost in the camera roll. Tap the Photo button on the home screen to add your first photo. 
2. **Prompts**: With a unique daily prompt, you never have to wonder “what should I write?” again. Tap the + (New) button on the home screen to find today’s prompt. 
3. **Today**: See your calendar events, location history, and photos all in one place to quickly recap your day in a summarized entry. Swipe right from the side of the home screen to access Today. 
4. **Privacy**: For your eyes only, the way a journal should be. Entries are encrypted, plus you can use Touch ID or Face ID to add an additional level of protection. 
5. **Unlimited Entries** Day One is a journal that’s impossible to fill up, but we encourage you to try. Tap the Text button on the home screen to create your first text entry. 
 
Looking to do even more with your journal? Here are five of our favorite **Premium features**:
 
1. **Video**: Become the director of your own highlight reel. Record video straight from Day One or add clips up to 5 minutes long from your camera roll. 
2. **Audio**: With audio recording, you can literally give your journal a voice—yours. Record with or without transcription. 
3. **Secure Sync**: Start an entry on one device, finish on another. It’s magic your thumbs will thank you for. 
4. **Instagram Importer**: Our slick importer tool automatically pulls (past and future) photos and videos from your Instagram account into Day One. 
5. **Cloud Backup**: Cloud backup gives you peace of mind that no matter what happens to your device, your entries are safe and sound on our secure servers.
 
 
Want to give Premium a try? [Tap here](dayone://premium) to start a free trial and gain access to the complete Day One Journal experience.
 
Need more help getting started? Our [help guides](https://help.dayoneapp.com) cover just about every topic and are accessible from the Settings menu right inside the Day One app.

# Rt 66 Trip
Arrived at the Marriott Chicago \(Oakbrook\)\.  Left home at about 1545\.

The hotel is up to full service Marriott standards, however it is showing its age\. It was here for all the time we lived in Clarendon Hills\.

The hotel is having some kind of Fred Astaire dance contest\. Lynn thinks the participants are gay\.

# Rt 66
Breakfast at Lou Mitchell’s\. Apple and cheddar omelette with toast and orange marmalade\.

47 miles\.

Joliet: Blues Brothers statue on the Rich & Creamy ice cream stand\.

Joliet RT66 Welcome Center museum was very interesting\. 

41 miles
Dwight: Ambler’s Texaco Station\.

9 miles
Odell: 1932 Standard Station\. Photo of Spike O’Dell\.

12 miles
Pontiac ILL: Rt 66 Hall of Fame Museum was a big disappointment\. The Wall Dog Mural museum was gone\. The only nice thing is that the town has many nice murals on the buildings\. But the Pontiac car museum was fun with many old Pontiacs on display\.

29 miles
Towanda: We drove parallel to the walking tour\. We were able to see the Burma Shave signs\.

9 miles
Normal ILL: 1931 Sprague Super Service Station was closed, but we took photos\.

Dinner at Distihl\. Very good beer and we both had delicious cuban sandwiches\.

We slept in a very nice Holiday Inn Express\.

entries.text:
RT 66
 24 miles
Atlanta, IL: We saw the 1908 Octagonal Library and the clock tower\. Hand wound clockworks visible through a window\.

46 miles
We managed to spend the whole day in Springfield\. The Lincoln Museum was wonderful\. We also toured the Lincoln home in the period neighborhood\. We waved goodby to the Lauterbach giant on the way out of Springfield\.

46 miles
Then we drove to Litchfield\. Ariston Cafe was closed Mondays\.

Dinner at Las Rancheros\. OK Mexican foods but portions way too big\. The restaurant wanted us to pay in cash\.

Slept at Holiday Inn Express\.

# RT 66
Breakfast at the Holiday Inn Express was the usual cereal and the delicious hot cinnamon rolls\.

Litchfield RT 66 museum was a very good experience\. 

9 miles
Mt Olive: Soulsby Shell Station\. It was open but there was no one there\. We got a good photo\.

69 miles
Museum of Transportation, Missouri\. Good experience\. The museum has many nicely done exhibits, especially the car museum\. The train exhibits were interesting, but the Pullman cars were not restored\.

14 miles
Chesterfield, MO\. Dinner at the Firefly Grill was pretty good\. Slept at a Holiday Inn express\.

Standard Holiday Inn breakfast\. 

13 miles
Eureka\. Drove past partly demolished Meramac River Bridge\. 

12 miles
Gray Summit\. Toured the Shaws Nature Reserve\. We walked the wildflower garden\. Then drove the Trail House Loop and saw two deer\. We enjoyed the Crescent Knoll overlook\.

24 miles
Merimac Caverns was ok\. 

6 miles
Stayed in Comfort Inn Sullivan\.  Dinner at Silo\. Lynn had grilled cheese, I had grilled chicken\.

entries.text:
# RT 66
6 miles
Drove from Sullivan to Bourbon\. Took a photo of the Bourbon water tower\.

12 miles 
Cuba, MO: Drove past the refurbished Wagon Wheel hotel\.

24 miles
Fanning, MO: Took photo of the world’s biggest rocking chair\.

59 miles
Lebanon, MO: Stopped at the Munger Moss Motel gift shop\. They have a guitar designed by Jessie McIntyre made in the shape of a Rt 66 sign that will be raffled off\. The guy who explained this to us says he knows Reeba McEntyre\. I had to walk a 3 inch curb in order to be eligible for the raffle and made it on the third try, but I still had to pay $5\.

55 miles
Springfield, MO: We drove past the Best Western Rt 66 Rail Haven motel, a Steak & Shake that is decorated with the original 
TAKHOMASACK signage\. We took a photo of the 1926 Gilloz Theater\.

58 mile scenic RT66
Carthage: We crossed over two very old bridges and saw Spencer, that might be a 1 block town\.

17 miles
Joplin, MO: Dinner at Wilder’s Steakhouse\. Slept at a Fairfield Inn\.

Hilton
I have 2 Hilton Honors accounts\. In 1Password, the one to continue using is called Hilton New\. I’m trying to transfer all points from Hilton Old and today put in a request to transfer 6000 points\. 

After a few days, I’ll check on the transfer\. If it’s successful I’ll put in a request to transfer the remaining 800\+\. If not successful, I need to call Hilton\.
